<subSubSection id="6DE165012516FF97FF451454FC72FA3E" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2544368A2516FF97FF451454FC72FA3E" blockId="3.[178,1086,1286,1425]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618">
Comment: The original description is based on 
<specimenCount id="33FDFD032516FF97FD201454FCA0FAB3" box="[727,818,1286,1308]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618" type="generic" typeStatus="type">five type</specimenCount>
specimens from &quot;Nanairi, southern Aizu, 
<collectingRegion id="E73FF8682516FF97FEA31471FD93FA96" box="[340,513,1315,1337]" country="Japan" name="Fukushima" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618">Fukushima Pref.</collectingRegion>
, Honshu&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="416A4B7B2516FF97FD801471FCAEFA96" author="WATANABE Y" box="[631,828,1315,1337]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618" pagination="358 - 363" refId="ref11698" refString="WATANABE Y. (2001 b): A new species of the group of Lathrobium brachypterum (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) from southern Aizu in northeastern Honshu, Japan. - Elytra, Tokyo 29 (2): 358 - 363." type="journal article" year="2001">WATANABE 2001b</bibRefCitation>
). Based on the similarly derived male sexual characters, 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D092516FF97FDD51410FD22FAF8" authorityName="WATANABE" authorityYear="2001" box="[546,688,1345,1367]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kurosawai">
<emphasis id="178FEA982516FF97FDD51410FD22FAF8" box="[546,688,1345,1367]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618">L. kurosawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is evidently closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D092516FF97FBDF1410FE4BFADB" authority="SHARP 1889" authorityName="SHARP" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachypterum">
<emphasis id="178FEA982516FF97FBDF1410FED2FADB" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618">L. brachypterum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="416A4B7B2516FF97FEA7140CFE4BFADB" author="SHARP D" box="[336,473,1374,1396]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618" pagination="463 - 476" refId="ref11439" refString="SHARP D. S. (1889): The Staphylinidae of Japan. - The Annals and Magazine of Natural History (6) 3: 28 - 44, 108 - 121, 249 - 267, 319 - 334, 406 - 419, 463 - 476." type="journal article" year="1889">SHARP 1889</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The above records reveal that the distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D092516FF97FBDF140DFE89FA3E" authorityName="WATANABE" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kurosawai">
<emphasis id="178FEA982516FF97FBDF140DFE89FA3E" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618">L. kurosawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not particularly restricted. The altitudes range from 
<quantity id="E2039B6F2516FF97FCB11429FC49FA3E" box="[838,987,1403,1425]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="11.5" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="1618" unit="m" value="800.0" valueMax="1150.0" valueMin="450.0">450 to 1150 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
